Citation.sTitle: Liquid liquid equilibrium for the ternary systems of water + methanol  + acrylonitrile
Citation.sAbstract: Liquid  liquid equilibrium data were measured for ternary system of methanol +  acrylonitrile + water at 288.15 K, 298.15 K and 313.15 K and atmospheric pressure. The consistency of the  experimental tie-line data has been confirmed by Othmer-Tobias correlation. The NRTL and UNIQUAC  models were applied to correlate the experimental data, and the calculated liquid liquid equilibrium data  using the regressed interation parameters agree well with the experimental data for the ternary system.
